<div class="container mt-4">
  <h2 class="text-center mt-4"><%= t("arclight.static_title") %></h2>
  <div class="row mt-4">
    <div class="col-md-6">
      <div class="card bg-light">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title text-center">Welcome to the Lyrasis Arclight Demo Site</h5>
          <p class="card-text">ArcLight is an open-source discovery and access application designed specifically for archival description and finding aids. It is built on the Blacklight framework (which itself is based on Ruby on Rails and Solr), and is intended to provide a modern, user-friendly interface for exploring archival collections.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
      <div class="card bg-light">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title text-center">What ArcLight Does</h5>
          <p class="card-text">ArcLight allows users to:</p>
          <p class="card-text">
            <ul>
              <li>Browse and search EAD (Encoded Archival Description) finding aids</li>
              <li>Navigate hierarchical archival structures (collection > series > files > items)</li>
              <li>View rich metadata and digital object links</li>
              <li>Use facets (like subject, date, collection) to narrow search results</li>
              <li>Export citation-friendly data</li>
            </ul>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr/>
  <div class="row mt-4">
    <div class="col-md-12">
      <div class="card bg-light">
        <div class="card-body text-center">
          <h5 class="card-title text-center">Technical Overview</h5>
          <p class="card-text">Framework: Built with Ruby on Rails using Blacklight</p>
          <p class="card-text">Search: Powered by Solr</p>
          <p class="card-text">Data Source: EAD XML files, indexed via Traject</p>
          <p class="card-text">Indexing Tool: Uses a Ruby gem called traject to transform EAD into Solr documents</p>
          <p class="card-text">UI: Highly customizable interface for end-user browsing/searching of archival collections</p>        
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
